    "description": "Extracted from sea water or brine by solar evaporation and crystallization. Can also be produced by reacting magnesium hydroxide or carbonate with hydrochloric acid. Traditional 'nigari' is made by evaporating sea water to remove sodium chloride, leaving a magnesium-rich brine."
