  "fun_facts": [
    "Known as 'NIGARI' in Japan - the traditional and preferred coagulant for making tofu for over 2,000 years",
    "Nigari is literally the leftover brine from making sea salt - waste product turned culinary treasure",
    "Different coagulants make different tofu textures: nigari makes smoother, sweeter tofu than calcium-based coagulants",
    "The second most abundant mineral in sea water after sodium chloride",
    "Used in the same form (as bath salts) for muscle relaxation and as a food ingredient for tofu",
    "Can have a slightly bitter taste, which is why 'nigari tofu' has a subtle sweetness - the bitterness is cooked out",
    "Traditional Japanese tofu masters can tell the quality of nigari by tasting the brine"
  ]
